# Authoritative for v6-only.demo. — the IPv6-only-NS pattern per
# spec 006 US3 / FR-015 (b). The container runs at a v4 address
# (172.31.0.16) on the demo's IPv4-only Compose network. The "v6-
# only-ness" lives in the *delegation* — the root zone advertises
# AAAA glue only for this zone's NSs (no A glue) — and in the
# auth-side records below (AAAA only for ns1 / ns2). The exporter's
# address_overrides route the v6 lookups back to this container
# via v4.

v6-only.demo. {
    file /zones/v6-only.demo.zone
    log
    errors
}
